FindMyMac
=========

FindMyMac is a PHP script that reports your Mac status, including:
*   latitude, longitude, country, city
*   address (requires Wi-Fi to be turned on)
*   public IP address (could help identify the ISP)
*   date of report
*   screenshot (see what the user is doing)
*   photo (see who is using the computer)

Reports are sent by e-mail.

Requirements
------------
MacOSX 10.6 (untested with other versions)

Included 3rd-party software
---------------------------
ImageSnap is a public domain command-line tool.
See: http://www.iharder.net/current/macosx/imagesnap/

License
